# Rotten Tomatoes Enrichment Pipeline

## Overview

RT enrichment stamps five fields onto Redis media documents by matching against a local on-disk RT content index. An optional Algolia live-search fallback is available for backfill scripts only.

Accepted RT matches must pass strict title, media type, and release-year validation before any RT metadata is applied. Do not accept nearest/fuzzy Algolia results or vanity hits from `external_ids.rt_id` unless the resolved RT record still strictly matches the source media document.

## RT Fields on Redis Document

| Field | Type | Source |
|---|---|---|
| `rt_audience_score` | `int \| null` | RT audience score |
| `rt_critics_score` | `int \| null` | RT critics score |
| `rt_vanity` | `str \| null` | RT URL slug (e.g. `the_matrix`) |
| `rt_release_year` | `int \| null` | RT release year |
| `rt_runtime` | `int \| null` | RT runtime in minutes |

Additionally, `external_ids.rt_id` (e.g. `m/the_matrix`) and `external_ids.tms_id` are back-populated on match.

## 3-Tier Matching Strategy

1. **Vanity lookup** (O(1)): If `external_ids.rt_id` exists, strip the `m/` or `tv/` prefix and look up directly in the vanity index. The resolved record must still pass strict title/type/year validation.
2. **Title + year**: Normalize title text and look up in the local title index with year filtering. Only strict title/type/year matches may be applied.
3. **Algolia fallback** (backfill only): Live search RT Algolia API with server-side `type:movie` or `type:tv` filtering. Results are cached into the local index for future runs only after strict validation.

## Key Files

- `src/api/rottentomatoes/local_store.py` — Local on-disk RT content index with title and vanity lookups.
- `src/etl/rt_enrichment.py` — Enrichment module: `enrich_redis_doc()` (sync, ETL), `enrich_from_local()`, `enrich_from_algolia()` (async).
- `src/etl/tmdb_nightly_etl.py` — ETL integration: calls `enrich_redis_doc()` after `document_to_redis()`, local-only (no Algolia).
- `scripts/backfill_rt_enrichment.py` — Standalone backfill with missing-data enrichment and `--audit-existing` remediation.
- `src/core/normalize.py` — `SearchDocument` dataclass and `document_to_redis()` carry the RT fields.

## Local RT Data

- `data/rt/content_index.json` — Pre-built content index (~3.5M lines). Contains `records` dict and `title_index` dict.
- `data/rt/content_all.jsonl` — Raw consolidated JSONL crawl output.
- `data/rt/dynamic/content_insertions.json` — JSONL log of dynamically inserted hits from Algolia fallback.

## Makefile Targets

- `make backfill-rt` — Run RT backfill (local-only by default).
- `make backfill-rt ARGS="--algolia-fallback"` — With Algolia fallback.
- `make backfill-rt ARGS="--dry-run"` — Discovery only.
- `make backfill-rt MC_TYPE=movie` — Filter to movies only.
- `make backfill-rt ARGS="--audit-existing --dry-run"` — Audit existing RT metadata without writing.
- `make backfill-rt ARGS="--audit-existing --algolia-fallback --push-to-mm"` — Repair or clear invalid existing RT metadata and propagate metadata changes.
- `make backfill-rt ARGS="--force"` — With `--push-to-mm`, send docs that already have RT data even when no Redis patch is needed.

## Existing Bad Data Remediation

Use `--audit-existing` when the goal is to fix documents that already have incorrect RT metadata. This mode scans RT-bearing documents, validates the current RT attachment with the same strict title/type/year matcher, and then:

- leaves valid RT metadata unchanged,
- attempts strict local title/year re-enrichment for invalid attachments,
- optionally attempts strict Algolia re-enrichment when `--algolia-fallback` is set,
- clears RT fields and `external_ids.rt_id` when no strict match exists,
- pushes repaired or cleared metadata to Media Manager when `--push-to-mm` is set.

Run audit dry-runs before writes:

```bash
make backfill-rt MC_TYPE=tv ARGS="--audit-existing --dry-run"
make backfill-rt MC_TYPE=tv ARGS="--audit-existing --algolia-fallback --dry-run"
```

Apply with Media Manager propagation only after reviewing dry-run counts:

```bash
make backfill-rt MC_TYPE=tv ARGS="--audit-existing --algolia-fallback --push-to-mm"
```

## ETL Integration

In `tmdb_nightly_etl.py`, `enrich_redis_doc_with_fallback(redis_doc)` is awaited after `document_to_redis(doc)` on every media item (not persons). This uses the full 3-tier matching strategy: local vanity lookup (tier 1), local title+year match (tier 2), and Algolia live search fallback (tier 3). Algolia results are cached into the local index for future runs.

## Propagation to Media Manager

Use `--push-to-mm` on the backfill script to propagate enriched docs inline:

```bash
make backfill-rt ARGS="--push-to-mm"
```

This sends each enriched doc to Media Manager's `/insert-docs` with `metadata_only=True`, which updates only the stored FAISS metadata (RT scores, external IDs, etc.) without re-running Wikipedia enrichment, LLM summarisation, or Voyage embedding generation. Documents not already in the FAISS index automatically fall through to the full pipeline.

Enriched docs are batched (100 per request) and sent as the backfill progresses. The remaining buffer is flushed at the end. Stats include `mm_queued`, `mm_skipped`, and `mm_errors`.
